      "message": "it matters when the message can be nil, e.g. in validation code. That\u0027s why GetXXX functions exist. I generally try to use the simplest tool for the job (just fields, not GetXXX), but sometimes GetXXX is required and/or makes the code easier to read (no need to extra nil checks). \n\nhere, in may not possible be nil\n\nWDYT?\n\n--\n\nanyway, this discussion applies to all code in resultdb, not specific to this CL. I think we can continue discussing this, e.g. in ML, and if we decide to change things, then we can make one large CL that changes all code in resultdb.",
